# Inventory Reports Implementation Plan

## Background

The deep research document identifies key inventory analytics for distribution businesses. This plan implements **4 new report endpoints** covering the most actionable reports not already served by the existing [Inventory.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Shofiq/Documents/0%20work/Shoudagor_Fullstack/shoudagor_FE/src/pages/reports/Inventory.tsx) / `/reports/inventory` page (which already has: inventory KPI ribbon, timeline chart, aging report, safety stock / ABC analysis). 

The 4 reports to implement are based on the highest-impact sections of the research document:

| Report | Research Section | Key Business Value |
|---|---|---|
| **Warehouse Summary** | "Warehouse Summary and Real-Time Status Report" | Stock position per warehouse/location – prevents overselling |
| **Inventory Valuation** | "Inventory Valuation and Cost Management Reports" | Financial snapshot of inventory asset value |
| **DSI & GMROI** | "Days Sales of Inventory and GMROI" | Identifies cash trapped in slow stock vs. profitable items |
| **Dead Stock** | "Obsolete and Dead Stock Reports" | Surfaces items with zero movement for disposal/clearance |

These complement the existing Aging/Safety-stock/ABC reports already in production.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

---

#### [MODIFY] [inventory_reports.py](file:///c:/Users/Shofiq/Documents/0%20work/Shoudagor_Fullstack/Shoudagor/app/repositories/reports/inventory_reports.py)

Adds 4 new repository methods with raw SQL:

1. **`get_warehouse_summary(company_id, start_date, end_date)`**  
   Queries `warehouse.inventory_stock ← warehouse.storage_location ← inventory.product ← inventory.product_variant ← inventory.product_price`. Returns per-location stock: `location_id, location_name, product_id, product_name, sku, beginning_balance, total_receipts, total_dispatches, committed_stock, current_stock, current_inventory_value`.

2. **`get_inventory_valuation(company_id)`**  
   Uses existing LIFO purchase pattern (from [get_inventory_kpi_ribbon_data](file:///c:/Users/Shofiq/Documents/0%20work/Shoudagor_Fullstack/Shoudagor/app/services/reports.py#30-49)) but broken down per product/variant. Returns: `product_id, product_name, sku, variant_id, quantity_on_hand, unit_cost, total_cost_value, total_selling_value, total_retail_value`.

3. **`get_dsi_gmroi_report(company_id, start_date, end_date)`**  
   **DSI** = (Average Inventory Value / COGS) × 365. **GMROI** = Gross Profit / Avg Inventory Cost. Queries sales orders + purchase prices per category. Returns: `category_id, category_name, cogs, avg_inventory_value, gross_profit, dsi, gmroi`.

4. **`get_dead_stock_report(company_id, days_threshold)`**  
   Items with zero sales in last N days AND positive current stock. Uses `warehouse.inventory_stock`, `sales.sales_order_detail`. Returns: `product_id, product_name, sku, variant_id, current_stock, unit_value, total_value, last_sale_date, days_since_last_sale`.

